Full-Time
FEMALE HR Manager – UAE experience is required
–
Abu Dhabi, Abu Dhabi, United Arab Emirates
Job Description
Responsibilities
Support the operations in recruitment, induction, employee relations and performance including absence management and retention of office and blue collar employees.
Develop new policies and procedures and revise existing one
Advise on remuneration, benefits and promotions
Support managers in succession planning
Managing employee relations and performance issues to ensure that the statutory law and company policies are adhered to and conducting disciplinaries, grievances and investigations
Preparing management reports
Skills & Experience
8 – 15 years HR experience with a minimum of 3 – 5 years HR management in the UAE, Gulf or Middle East
Experience of working in an organisation of over 1,000 employees in the Middle East preferably in engineering, hospitality, FMCG organisations
Fluency in English is essential
Excellent working knowledge of UAE labour practices and standards
Education
Bachelors Degree – preferably in HR
Candidate Profile
Indian female
Aged between 32 – 40 years
How to Apply
